            <div type="transcript" id="P91-110">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>A THUNDER-STORM.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The wind begun to rock the grass</l>
                    <l>With threatening tunes and low, </l>
                    <l>He flung a menace at the earth,</l>
                    <l>A menace at the sky.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The leaves unhooked themselves from trees</l>
                    <l>And started all abroad;</l>
                    <l>The dust did scoop itself like hands</l>
                    <l>And throw away the road.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The wagons quickened on the streets,</l>
                    <l>The thunder hurried slow;</l>
                    <l>The lightning showed a yellow beak,</l>
                    <l>And then a livid claw.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The birds put up the bars to nests,</l>
                    <l>The cattle fled to barns;</l>
                    <l>There came one drop of giant rain,</l>
                    <l>And then, as if the hands</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>That held the dams had parted hold,</l>
                    <l>The waters wrecked the sky,</l>
                    <l>But overlooked my father's house,</l>
                    <l>Just quartering a tree.</l>
                </lg>

            </div>     
